---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Mozambique Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/mozambique/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'South Africa for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/south-africa' },
  { title: 'Tanzania for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/tanzania' },
  { title: 'Portugal for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/portugal' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'mozambiqueFit', header: 'Mozambique Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MZN$32,000-45,700/mo', mozambiqueFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MZN$37,400-53,400/mo', mozambiqueFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MZN$28,800-41,100/mo', mozambiqueFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'MZN$26,800-38,300/mo', mozambiqueFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Fidelidade)', entryAge: '60', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'MZN$5,000-15,000/mo', mozambiqueFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'MZN$28,800-45,700', annual: 'MZN$345.6K-548.4K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'MZN$39,500-61,000', annual: 'MZN$474K-732K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'MZN$53,100-81,850', annual: 'MZN$637.2K-982.2K' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'MZN$2,000-6,000/visit', annual: 'Affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'MZN$10,000-30,000/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Mozambique 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Mozambique. Portuguese language, Indian Ocean beaches, safari, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Mozambique"
  subheadline="Mozambique offers stunning Indian Ocean beaches, Portuguese language, diverse wildlife, and affordable living—a beautiful coastal African destination recovering from past challenges."
  heroImage="/images/countries/mozambique-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Mozambique</h2>
  <p>
    Mozambique offers beautiful Indian Ocean beaches, Portuguese language (for Portuguese/Brazilian speakers), diverse wildlife, and affordable living. For Portuguese-speaking retirees seeking African beach paradise with good value, Mozambique provides unique option with natural beauty.
  </p>

  <p>
    Maputo is the capital with best healthcare and Portuguese colonial architecture. Vilankulo/Bazaruto offer beach paradise and diving. Pemba provides northern beach access. Gorongosa has wildlife. Most expats choose Maputo for healthcare; beaches for lifestyle.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; South Africa backup essential</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Portuguese (official); English growing</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> MZN$60,000-120,000/month (~$940-1,880 USD); moderate</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; wet season Nov-Apr</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Portuguese heritage; beach culture; developing</li>
      <li><strong>South Africa access:</strong> Johannesburg 1-hour flight from Maputo</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Mozambique Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Mozambique healthcare is limited—Clinic Sommerschield in Maputo is main private option. Public healthcare underfunded. Most complex cases evacuate to South Africa (Johannesburg 1-hour flight from Maputo). Beach areas have very basic healthcare. Portuguese-speaking doctors available.
  </p>

  <p>
    Healthcare improving but from low base. Private care in Maputo reasonable for routine needs. International insurance with South Africa evacuation essential. Don't rely on local healthcare for serious conditions.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">South Africa Backup Essential</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      South Africa provides essential medical backup—Johannesburg is 1-hour flight from Maputo with world-class hospitals. Beach areas require evacuation to Maputo then South Africa. Include South Africa in insurance coverage. Healthcare limitations are real.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Mozambique has accessible visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    30-day visa available on arrival or e-visa for many nationalities. Extensions possible.
  </p>

  <h3>Short-Stay Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For visits up to 90 days. Apply through Mozambique embassy.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Visa (DIRE)</h3>
  <p>
    For longer stays. Various categories including retirement. Requires documentation and investment proof.
  </p>

  <h3>Investment Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For business investment. Some retirees use this with property purchase.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Mozambique:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> South Africa coverage critical</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Mozambique</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with strong South Africa evacuation coverage essential. Maputo private care handles routine needs. Beach areas need evacuation to Maputo then South Africa. Don't economize—healthcare limitations are real. Portuguese-speaking support helpful.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Mozambique, South Africa evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Mozambique</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Southern Africa network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>South Africa access:</strong> World-class healthcare nearby</li>
    <li><strong>Portuguese support:</strong> Language assistance helpful</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage with South Africa evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Mozambique (MZN ~64 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Maputo base:</strong> Best local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>South Africa network:</strong> Use for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Routine care affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Regional plans:</strong> Southern Africa focused</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Portuguese Beach Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> €2,000/month pension. Residence visa. Vilankulo.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Portugal and South Africa coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MZN$35,000/month (~$545). Portuguese ease; comprehensive backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: South African Neighbor, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> ZAR$35,000/month pension. Residence visa. Maputo.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with South Africa home coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MZN$45,000/month (~$700). Border proximity; home backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Brazilian Explorer, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> R$12,000/month income. Tourist visa rotation. Pemba.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with evacuation to Johannesburg.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~MZN$30,000/month (~$470). Portuguese language; remote location.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Portuguese?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Essential outside Maputo—Portuguese is official language. English limited, growing in business/tourism. Healthcare predominantly Portuguese. Learning Portuguese important for daily life and medical situations. Brazilians/Portuguese have advantage.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Mozambique safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally safe but requires awareness—petty crime in cities. Northern insurgency in Cabo Delgado province (avoid). Tourist areas well-managed. Beach resorts secure. Normal precautions apply. Check current situation before travel.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What are the beaches like?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Stunning—2,500km Indian Ocean coastline. Bazaruto Archipelago is premier destination. Tofo/Vilankulo offer excellent diving. Pemba has pristine northern beaches. Less developed than Thailand/Bali—more authentic, less infrastructure.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How developed is Mozambique?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Developing—recovering from civil war (ended 1992). Infrastructure improving but limited. Power outages common outside Maputo. Roads can be challenging. Beach resorts have good amenities. Expect adventure not convenience.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Mozambique coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Mozambique authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
